{
  "id": "phekb-heart-failure-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "heart-failure",
  "name": "Heart Failure - Comprehensive Provider Query",
  "description": "Simulates a cardiologist identifying their complete heart failure population for a quality improvement initiative. The PheKB HF algorithm requires evidence from three orthogonal sources: ICD diagnosis codes, structured/NLP problem list mentions, and ejection fraction measurements (categorizes definite, probable, possible HF). Real-world identification primarily uses the union of: HF diagnosis codes, GDMT prescriptions, and EF<50% on echo. A Condition-only query underestimates the population.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete heart failure patient population for a guideline-directed medical therapy (GDMT) optimization initiative. From clinical experience, I know HF patients are documented in different ways: some have a formal diagnosis code (CHF, HFrEF, HFpEF), some are on classic HF medications (loop diuretics, ARNi, SGLT2 inhibitors, MRAs) without a formal HF diagnosis, and some have a documented reduced ejection fraction on echo.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any heart failure diagnosis (CHF, HFrEF, HFpEF, or general heart failure)\n2. Patients prescribed HF medications (sacubitril/valsartan, carvedilol, spironolactone, empagliflozin, furosemide)\n3. Patients with echocardiogram ejection fraction measurements below 50 percent\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found across these three approaches.",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of HF dx codes (Paths A+B), HF GDMT (Paths A+C), and reduced-EF observations (Paths A+D for HFrEF). Tests provider-level identification across orthogonal evidence streams. The PheKB algorithm's 'definite/probable/possible' classification is operationalized here as union of evidence.",
    "expected_queries": [
      "Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|84114007,http://snomed.info/sct|42343007,http://snomed.info/sct|88805009,http://snomed.info/sct|703272007,http://snomed.info/sct|446221000",
      "MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|4603,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|20352,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|9997,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|1656339,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|1545653",
      "Observation?code=http://loinc.org|8806-2&value-quantity=lt50"
    ],
